name: drive
title: Drive API
description: Manages files in Drive including uploading, downloading, searching, detecting changes, and updating sharing permissions.

parameters.name: userIp
parameters.desc: IP address of the site where the request originates. Use this if you want to enforce per-user limits.

parameters.name: fields
parameters.desc: Selector specifying which fields to include in a partial response.

parameters.name: key
parameters.desc: API key. Your API key identifies your project and provides you with API access, quota, and reports. Required unless you provide an OAuth 2.0 token.

parameters.name: oauth_token
parameters.desc: OAuth 2.0 token for the current user.

parameters.name: prettyPrint
parameters.desc: Returns response with indentations and line breaks.

parameters.name: quotaUser
parameters.desc: Available to use for quota purposes for server-side applications. Can be any arbitrary string assigned to a user, but should not exceed 40 characters. Overrides userIp if both are provided.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Identifies what kind of resource this is. Value: the fixed string "drive#startPageToken".

fields.name: startPageToken
fields.desc: The starting page token for listing changes.

fields.name: permissionId
fields.desc: The user's ID as visible in Permission resources.

fields.name: photoLink
fields.desc: A link to the user's profile photo, if available.

fields.name: displayName
fields.desc: A plain text displayable name for this user.

fields.name: emailAddress
fields.desc: The email address of the user. This may not be present in certain contexts if the user has not made their email address visible to the requester.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Identifies what kind of resource this is. Value: the fixed string "drive#user".

fields.name: me
fields.desc: Whether this user is the requesting user.

schemas.name: About
schemas.desc: Information about the user, the user's Drive, and system capabilities.

fields.name: storageQuota
fields.desc: The user's storage quota limits and usage. All fields are measured in bytes.

fields.name: limit
fields.desc: The usage limit, if applicable. This will not be present if the user has unlimited storage.

fields.name: usage
fields.desc: The total usage across all services.

fields.name: usageInDrive
fields.desc: The usage by all files in Google Drive.

fields.name: usageInDriveTrash
fields.desc: The usage by trashed files in Google Drive.

fields.name: user
fields.desc: The authenticated user.

fields.name: exportFormats
fields.desc: A map of source MIME type to possible targets for all supported exports.

fields.name: folderColorPalette
fields.desc: The currently supported folder colors as RGB hex strings.

fields.name: importFormats
fields.desc: A map of source MIME type to possible targets for all supported imports.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Identifies what kind of resource this is. Value: the fixed string "drive#about".

fields.name: appInstalled
fields.desc: Whether the user has installed the requesting app.

fields.name: maxImportSizes
fields.desc: A map of maximum import sizes by MIME type, in bytes.

fields.name: maxUploadSize
fields.desc: The maximum upload size in bytes.

schemas.name: ChangeList
schemas.desc: A list of changes for a user.

fields.name: changes
fields.desc: The list of changes. If nextPageToken is populated, then this list may be incomplete and an additional page of results should be fetched.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Identifies what kind of resource this is. Value: the fixed string "drive#changeList".

fields.name: newStartPageToken
fields.desc: The starting page token for future changes. This will be present only if the end of the current changes list has been reached.

fields.name: nextPageToken
fields.desc: The page token for the next page of changes. This will be absent if the end of the changes list has been reached. If the token is rejected for any reason, it should be discarded, and pagination should be restarted from the first page of results.

schemas.name: GeneratedIds
schemas.desc: A list of generated file IDs which can be provided in create requests.

fields.name: ids
fields.desc: The IDs generated for the requesting user in the specified space.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Identifies what kind of resource this is. Value: the fixed string "drive#generatedIds".

fields.name: space
fields.desc: The type of file that can be created with these IDs.

schemas.name: Reply
schemas.desc: A reply to a comment on a file.

fields.name: action
fields.desc:
The action the reply performed to the parent comment. Valid values are:  
- resolve 
- reopen

fields.name: deleted
fields.desc: Whether the reply has been deleted. A deleted reply has no content.

fields.name: modifiedTime
fields.desc: The last time the reply was modified (RFC 3339 date-time).

fields.name: author
fields.desc: The user who created the reply.

fields.name: content
fields.desc: The plain text content of the reply. This field is used for setting the content, while htmlContent should be displayed. This is required on creates if no action is specified.

fields.name: createdTime
fields.desc: The time at which the reply was created (RFC 3339 date-time).

fields.name: htmlContent
fields.desc: The content of the reply with HTML formatting.

fields.name: id
fields.desc: The ID of the reply.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Identifies what kind of resource this is. Value: the fixed string "drive#reply".

schemas.name: RevisionList
schemas.desc: A list of revisions of a file.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Identifies what kind of resource this is. Value: the fixed string "drive#revisionList".

fields.name: nextPageToken
fields.desc: The page token for the next page of revisions. This will be absent if the end of the revisions list has been reached. If the token is rejected for any reason, it should be discarded, and pagination should be restarted from the first page of results.

fields.name: revisions
fields.desc: The list of revisions. If nextPageToken is populated, then this list may be incomplete and an additional page of results should be fetched.

fields.name: id
fields.desc: The ID of this Team Drive which is also the ID of the top level folder for this Team Drive.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Identifies what kind of resource this is. Value: the fixed string "drive#teamDrive".

fields.name: name
fields.desc: The name of this Team Drive.

fields.name: capabilities
fields.desc: Capabilities the current user has on this Team Drive.

fields.name: canComment
fields.desc: Whether the current user can comment on files in this Team Drive.

fields.name: canCopy
fields.desc: Whether files in this Team Drive can be copied by the current user.

fields.name: canManageMembers
fields.desc: Whether the current user can add members to this Team Drive or remove them or change their role.

fields.name: canReadRevisions
fields.desc: Whether the current user has read access to the Revisions resource of files in this Team Drive.

fields.name: canRemoveChildren
fields.desc: Whether the current user can remove children from folders in this Team Drive.

fields.name: canRename
fields.desc: Whether files or folders in this Team Drive can be renamed by the current user.

fields.name: canShare
fields.desc: Whether the current user can share files or folders in this Team Drive.

fields.name: canAddChildren
fields.desc: Whether the current user can add children to folders in this Team Drive.

fields.name: canDeleteTeamDrive
fields.desc: Whether this Team Drive can be deleted by the current user.

fields.name: canDownload
fields.desc: Whether files in this Team Drive can be downloaded by the current user.

fields.name: canEdit
fields.desc: Whether files in this Team Drive can be edited by the current user.

fields.name: canListChildren
fields.desc: Whether the current user can list the children of folders in this Team Drive.

fields.name: canRenameTeamDrive
fields.desc: Whether this Team Drive can be renamed by the current user.

fields.name: teamDrives
fields.desc: The list of Team Drives. If nextPageToken is populated, then this list may be incomplete and an additional page of results should be fetched.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Identifies what kind of resource this is. Value: the fixed string "drive#teamDriveList".

fields.name: nextPageToken
fields.desc: The page token for the next page of Team Drives. This will be absent if the end of the Team Drives list has been reached. If the token is rejected for any reason, it should be discarded, and pagination should be restarted from the first page of results.

schemas.name: CommentList
schemas.desc: A list of comments on a file.

fields.name: comments
fields.desc: The list of comments. If nextPageToken is populated, then this list may be incomplete and an additional page of results should be fetched.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Identifies what kind of resource this is. Value: the fixed string "drive#commentList".

fields.name: nextPageToken
fields.desc: The page token for the next page of comments. This will be absent if the end of the comments list has been reached. If the token is rejected for any reason, it should be discarded, and pagination should be restarted from the first page of results.

fields.name: description
fields.desc: A short description of the file.

fields.name: owners
fields.desc: The owners of the file. Currently, only certain legacy files may have more than one owner. Not populated for Team Drive files.

fields.name: hasAugmentedPermissions
fields.desc: Whether any users are granted file access directly on this file. This field is only populated for Team Drive files.

fields.name: sharingUser
fields.desc: The user who shared the file with the requesting user, if applicable.

fields.name: thumbnailLink
fields.desc: A short-lived link to the file's thumbnail, if available. Typically lasts on the order of hours. Only populated when the requesting app can access the file's content.

fields.name: webContentLink
fields.desc: A link for downloading the content of the file in a browser. This is only available for files with binary content in Drive.

fields.name: imageMediaMetadata
fields.desc: Additional metadata about image media, if available.

fields.name: rotation
fields.desc: The rotation in clockwise degrees from the image's original orientation.

fields.name: sensor
fields.desc: The type of sensor used to create the photo.

fields.name: cameraMake
fields.desc: The make of the camera used to create the photo.

fields.name: colorSpace
fields.desc: The color space of the photo.

fields.name: focalLength
fields.desc: The focal length used to create the photo, in millimeters.

fields.name: height
fields.desc: The height of the image in pixels.

fields.name: maxApertureValue
fields.desc: The smallest f-number of the lens at the focal length used to create the photo (APEX value).

fields.name: cameraModel
fields.desc: The model of the camera used to create the photo.

fields.name: exposureTime
fields.desc: The length of the exposure, in seconds.

fields.name: lens
fields.desc: The lens used to create the photo.

fields.name: location
fields.desc: Geographic location information stored in the image.

fields.name: altitude
fields.desc: The altitude stored in the image.

fields.name: latitude
fields.desc: The latitude stored in the image.

fields.name: longitude
fields.desc: The longitude stored in the image.

fields.name: exposureMode
fields.desc: The exposure mode used to create the photo.

fields.name: meteringMode
fields.desc: The metering mode used to create the photo.

fields.name: subjectDistance
fields.desc: The distance to the subject of the photo, in meters.

fields.name: whiteBalance
fields.desc: The white balance mode used to create the photo.

fields.name: time
fields.desc: The date and time the photo was taken (EXIF DateTime).

fields.name: width
fields.desc: The width of the image in pixels.

fields.name: aperture
fields.desc: The aperture used to create the photo (f-number).

fields.name: exposureBias
fields.desc: The exposure bias of the photo (APEX value).

fields.name: flashUsed
fields.desc: Whether a flash was used to create the photo.

fields.name: isoSpeed
fields.desc: The ISO speed used to create the photo.

fields.name: originalFilename
fields.desc: The original filename of the uploaded content if available, or else the original value of the name field. This is only available for files with binary content in Drive.

fields.name: permissions
fields.desc: The full list of permissions for the file. This is only available if the requesting user can share the file. Not populated for Team Drive files.

fields.name: sharedWithMeTime
fields.desc: The time at which the file was shared with the user, if applicable (RFC 3339 date-time).

fields.name: webViewLink
fields.desc: A link for opening the file in a relevant Google editor or viewer in a browser.

fields.name: teamDriveId
fields.desc: ID of the Team Drive the file resides in.

fields.name: appProperties
fields.desc:
A collection of arbitrary key-value pairs which are private to the requesting app.
Entries with null values are cleared in update and copy requests.

fields.name: hasThumbnail
fields.desc: Whether this file has a thumbnail.

fields.name: headRevisionId
fields.desc: The ID of the file's head revision. This is currently only available for files with binary content in Drive.

fields.name: lastModifyingUser
fields.desc: The last user to modify the file.

fields.name: md5Checksum
fields.desc: The MD5 checksum for the content of the file. This is only applicable to files with binary content in Drive.

fields.name: trashingUser
fields.desc: If the file has been explicitly trashed, the user who trashed it. Only populated for Team Drive files.

fields.name: viewedByMe
fields.desc: Whether the file has been viewed by this user.

fields.name: viewersCanCopyContent
fields.desc: Whether users with only reader or commenter permission can copy the file's content. This affects copy, download, and print operations.

fields.name: capabilities
fields.desc: Capabilities the current user has on the file. Each capability corresponds to a fine-grained action that a user may take.

fields.name: canComment
fields.desc: Whether the user can comment on the file.

fields.name: canMoveTeamDriveItem
fields.desc: Whether the user can move this Team Drive item by changing its parent. Note that a request to change the parent for this item may still fail depending on the new parent that is being added. Only populated for Team Drive files.

fields.name: canReadRevisions
fields.desc: Whether the user has read access to the Revisions resource of the file. For a Team Drive item, whether revisions of non-folder descendants of this item, or this item itself if it is not a folder, can be read.

fields.name: canReadTeamDrive
fields.desc: Whether the user has read access to the Team Drive to which this file belongs. Only populated for Team Drive files.

fields.name: canUntrash
fields.desc: Whether the file can be restored from the trash by the current user.

fields.name: canDownload
fields.desc: Whether the file can be downloaded by the user.

fields.name: canMoveItemIntoTeamDrive
fields.desc: Whether the current user can move this item into a Team Drive. If the item is in a Team Drive, this field is equivalent to canMoveTeamDriveItem.

fields.name: canRemoveChildren
fields.desc: Whether the user can remove children from this folder. This is always false when the item is not a folder.

fields.name: canAddChildren
fields.desc: Whether the user can add children to this folder. This is always false when the item is not a folder.

fields.name: canEdit
fields.desc: Whether the user can edit the file's content.

fields.name: canListChildren
fields.desc: Whether the user can list the children of this folder. This is always false when the item is not a folder.

fields.name: canRename
fields.desc: Whether the file can be renamed by the user.

fields.name: canTrash
fields.desc: Whether the file can be trashed by the user.

fields.name: canCopy
fields.desc: Whether the user can copy the file. For a Team Drive item, whether non-folder descendants of this item, or this item itself if it is not a folder, can be copied.

fields.name: canDelete
fields.desc: Whether the file can be deleted by the user.

fields.name: canShare
fields.desc: Whether the user can modify the file's permissions and sharing settings.

fields.name: fullFileExtension
fields.desc:
The full file extension extracted from the name field. May contain multiple concatenated extensions, such as "tar.gz". This is only available for files with binary content in Drive.
This is automatically updated when the name field changes, however it is not cleared if the new name does not contain a valid extension.

fields.name: id
fields.desc: The ID of the file.

fields.name: ownedByMe
fields.desc: Whether the user owns the file. Not populated for Team Drive files.

fields.name: quotaBytesUsed
fields.desc: The number of storage quota bytes used by the file. This includes the head revision as well as previous revisions with keepForever enabled.

fields.name: size
fields.desc: The size of the file's content in bytes. This is only applicable to files with binary content in Drive.

fields.name: spaces
fields.desc: The list of spaces which contain the file. The currently supported values are 'drive', 'appDataFolder' and 'photos'.

fields.name: contentHints
fields.desc: Additional information about the content of the file. These fields are never populated in responses.

fields.name: indexableText
fields.desc: Text to be indexed for the file to improve fullText queries. This is limited to 128KB in length and may contain HTML elements.

fields.name: thumbnail
fields.desc: A thumbnail for the file. This will only be used if Drive cannot generate a standard thumbnail.

fields.name: mimeType
fields.desc: The MIME type of the thumbnail.

fields.name: image
fields.desc: The thumbnail data encoded with URL-safe Base64 (RFC 4648 section 5).

fields.name: folderColorRgb
fields.desc:
The color for a folder as an RGB hex string. The supported colors are published in the folderColorPalette field of the About resource.
If an unsupported color is specified, the closest color in the palette will be used instead.

fields.name: mimeType
fields.desc:
The MIME type of the file.
Drive will attempt to automatically detect an appropriate value from uploaded content if no value is provided. The value cannot be changed unless a new revision is uploaded.
If a file is created with a Google Doc MIME type, the uploaded content will be imported if possible. The supported import formats are published in the About resource.

fields.name: modifiedByMe
fields.desc: Whether the file has been modified by this user.

fields.name: properties
fields.desc:
A collection of arbitrary key-value pairs which are visible to all apps.
Entries with null values are cleared in update and copy requests.

fields.name: starred
fields.desc: Whether the user has starred the file.

fields.name: trashedTime
fields.desc: The time that the item was trashed (RFC 3339 date-time). Only populated for Team Drive files.

fields.name: version
fields.desc: A monotonically increasing version number for the file. This reflects every change made to the file on the server, even those not visible to the user.

fields.name: fileExtension
fields.desc: The final component of fullFileExtension. This is only available for files with binary content in Drive.

fields.name: isAppAuthorized
fields.desc: Whether the file was created or opened by the requesting app.

fields.name: modifiedByMeTime
fields.desc: The last time the file was modified by the user (RFC 3339 date-time).

fields.name: modifiedTime
fields.desc:
The last time the file was modified by anyone (RFC 3339 date-time).
Note that setting modifiedTime will also update modifiedByMeTime for the user.

fields.name: name
fields.desc: The name of the file. This is not necessarily unique within a folder. Note that for immutable items such as the top level folders of Team Drives, My Drive root folder, and Application Data folder the name is constant.

fields.name: videoMediaMetadata
fields.desc: Additional metadata about video media. This may not be available immediately upon upload.

fields.name: durationMillis
fields.desc: The duration of the video in milliseconds.

fields.name: height
fields.desc: The height of the video in pixels.

fields.name: width
fields.desc: The width of the video in pixels.

fields.name: viewedByMeTime
fields.desc: The last time the file was viewed by the user (RFC 3339 date-time).

fields.name: shared
fields.desc: Whether the file has been shared. Not populated for Team Drive files.

fields.name: thumbnailVersion
fields.desc: The thumbnail version for use in thumbnail cache invalidation.

fields.name: trashed
fields.desc: Whether the file has been trashed, either explicitly or from a trashed parent folder. Only the owner may trash a file, and other users cannot see files in the owner's trash.

fields.name: createdTime
fields.desc: The time at which the file was created (RFC 3339 date-time).

fields.name: explicitlyTrashed
fields.desc: Whether the file has been explicitly trashed, as opposed to recursively trashed from a parent folder.

fields.name: iconLink
fields.desc: A static, unauthenticated link to the file's icon.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Identifies what kind of resource this is. Value: the fixed string "drive#file".

fields.name: parents
fields.desc:
The IDs of the parent folders which contain the file.
If not specified as part of a create request, the file will be placed directly in the My Drive folder. Update requests must use the addParents and removeParents parameters to modify the values.

fields.name: writersCanShare
fields.desc: Whether users with only writer permission can modify the file's permissions. Not populated for Team Drive files.

schemas.name: Permission
schemas.desc: A permission for a file. A permission grants a user, group, domain or the world access to a file or a folder hierarchy.

fields.name: domain
fields.desc: The domain to which this permission refers.

fields.name: expirationTime
fields.desc:
The time at which this permission will expire (RFC 3339 date-time). Expiration times have the following restrictions:  
- They can only be set on user and group permissions 
- The time must be in the future 
- The time cannot be more than a year in the future

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Identifies what kind of resource this is. Value: the fixed string "drive#permission".

fields.name: role
fields.desc:
The role granted by this permission. While new values may be supported in the future, the following are currently allowed:  
- organizer 
- owner 
- writer 
- commenter 
- reader

fields.name: allowFileDiscovery
fields.desc: Whether the permission allows the file to be discovered through search. This is only applicable for permissions of type domain or anyone.

fields.name: displayName
fields.desc: A displayable name for users, groups or domains.

fields.name: photoLink
fields.desc: A link to the user's profile photo, if available.

fields.name: teamDrivePermissionDetails
fields.desc: Details of whether the Permissions on this Team Drive item are inherited or directly on this item. This is an output-only field which is present only for Team Drive items.

fields.name: role
fields.desc:
The primary role for this user. While new values may be added in the future, the following are currently possible:  
- organizer 
- writer 
- commenter 
- reader

fields.name: teamDrivePermissionType
fields.desc:
The Team Drive permission type for this user. While new values may be added in future, the following are currently possible:  
- file
- 
- member

fields.name: inherited
fields.desc: Whether this permission is inherited. This field is always populated. This is an output-only field.

fields.name: inheritedFrom
fields.desc: The ID of the item from which this permission is inherited. This is an output-only field and is only populated for members of the Team Drive.

fields.name: type
fields.desc:
The type of the grantee. Valid values are:  
- user 
- group 
- domain 
- anyone

fields.name: emailAddress
fields.desc: The email address of the user or group to which this permission refers.

fields.name: id
fields.desc: The ID of this permission. This is a unique identifier for the grantee, and is published in User resources as permissionId.

schemas.name: Revision
schemas.desc: The metadata for a revision to a file.

fields.name: id
fields.desc: The ID of the revision.

fields.name: lastModifyingUser
fields.desc: The last user to modify this revision.

fields.name: originalFilename
fields.desc: The original filename used to create this revision. This is only applicable to files with binary content in Drive.

fields.name: publishedOutsideDomain
fields.desc: Whether this revision is published outside the domain. This is only applicable to Google Docs.

fields.name: publishAuto
fields.desc: Whether subsequent revisions will be automatically republished. This is only applicable to Google Docs.

fields.name: published
fields.desc: Whether this revision is published. This is only applicable to Google Docs.

fields.name: size
fields.desc: The size of the revision's content in bytes. This is only applicable to files with binary content in Drive.

fields.name: keepForever
fields.desc:
Whether to keep this revision forever, even if it is no longer the head revision. If not set, the revision will be automatically purged 30 days after newer content is uploaded. This can be set on a maximum of 200 revisions for a file.
This field is only applicable to files with binary content in Drive.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Identifies what kind of resource this is. Value: the fixed string "drive#revision".

fields.name: md5Checksum
fields.desc: The MD5 checksum of the revision's content. This is only applicable to files with binary content in Drive.

fields.name: mimeType
fields.desc: The MIME type of the revision.

fields.name: modifiedTime
fields.desc: The last time the revision was modified (RFC 3339 date-time).

fields.name: incompleteSearch
fields.desc: Whether the search process was incomplete. If true, then some search results may be missing, since all documents were not searched. This may occur when searching multiple Team Drives with the "user,allTeamDrives" corpora, but all corpora could not be searched. When this happens, it is suggested that clients narrow their query by choosing a different corpus such as "user" or "teamDrive".

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Identifies what kind of resource this is. Value: the fixed string "drive#fileList".

fields.name: nextPageToken
fields.desc: The page token for the next page of files. This will be absent if the end of the files list has been reached. If the token is rejected for any reason, it should be discarded, and pagination should be restarted from the first page of results.

fields.name: files
fields.desc: The list of files. If nextPageToken is populated, then this list may be incomplete and an additional page of results should be fetched.

schemas.name: ReplyList
schemas.desc: A list of replies to a comment on a file.

fields.name: replies
fields.desc: The list of replies. If nextPageToken is populated, then this list may be incomplete and an additional page of results should be fetched.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Identifies what kind of resource this is. Value: the fixed string "drive#replyList".

fields.name: nextPageToken
fields.desc: The page token for the next page of replies. This will be absent if the end of the replies list has been reached. If the token is rejected for any reason, it should be discarded, and pagination should be restarted from the first page of results.

schemas.name: Change
schemas.desc: A change to a file or Team Drive.

fields.name: removed
fields.desc: Whether the file or Team Drive has been removed from this list of changes, for example by deletion or loss of access.

fields.name: teamDrive
fields.desc: The updated state of the Team Drive. Present if the type is teamDrive, the user is still a member of the Team Drive, and the Team Drive has not been removed.

fields.name: teamDriveId
fields.desc: The ID of the Team Drive associated with this change.

fields.name: time
fields.desc: The time of this change (RFC 3339 date-time).

fields.name: type
fields.desc: The type of the change. Possible values are file and teamDrive.

fields.name: file
fields.desc: The updated state of the file. Present if the type is file and the file has not been removed from this list of changes.

fields.name: fileId
fields.desc: The ID of the file which has changed.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Identifies what kind of resource this is. Value: the fixed string "drive#change".

schemas.name: Channel
schemas.desc: An notification channel used to watch for resource changes.

fields.name: token
fields.desc: An arbitrary string delivered to the target address with each notification delivered over this channel. Optional.

fields.name: address
fields.desc: The address where notifications are delivered for this channel.

fields.name: id
fields.desc: A UUID or similar unique string that identifies this channel.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Identifies this as a notification channel used to watch for changes to a resource. Value: the fixed string "api#channel".

fields.name: params
fields.desc: Additional parameters controlling delivery channel behavior. Optional.

fields.name: type
fields.desc: The type of delivery mechanism used for this channel.

fields.name: expiration
fields.desc: Date and time of notification channel expiration, expressed as a Unix timestamp, in milliseconds. Optional.

fields.name: payload
fields.desc: A Boolean value to indicate whether payload is wanted. Optional.

fields.name: resourceId
fields.desc: An opaque ID that identifies the resource being watched on this channel. Stable across different API versions.

fields.name: resourceUri
fields.desc: A version-specific identifier for the watched resource.

fields.name: replies
fields.desc: The full list of replies to the comment in chronological order.

fields.name: resolved
fields.desc: Whether the comment has been resolved by one of its replies.

fields.name: anchor
fields.desc: A region of the document represented as a JSON string. See anchor documentation for details on how to define and interpret anchor properties.

fields.name: author
fields.desc: The user who created the comment.

fields.name: content
fields.desc: The plain text content of the comment. This field is used for setting the content, while htmlContent should be displayed.

fields.name: deleted
fields.desc: Whether the comment has been deleted. A deleted comment has no content.

fields.name: htmlContent
fields.desc: The content of the comment with HTML formatting.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Identifies what kind of resource this is. Value: the fixed string "drive#comment".

fields.name: createdTime
fields.desc: The time at which the comment was created (RFC 3339 date-time).

fields.name: id
fields.desc: The ID of the comment.

fields.name: modifiedTime
fields.desc: The last time the comment or any of its replies was modified (RFC 3339 date-time).

fields.name: quotedFileContent
